 "text": "When booting from the install CD, the kernel panics with: \n\npanic: No BIOS smap info from loader\nUptime 1s\n\nIrrespective of options (safe mode, single user, acpi disabled/enabled), (w) or w/out USB keyboard/mouse (PS/2 tried just in case), the kernel panics after the menu screen.\n\nThe machine is a HP dc5750 SFF with ATI X-Press 1150 chipset, 2GB DDR2 RAM (more details, of course in the \"lspci -vxxx\" output farther down.).  The BIOS is the newest from April 7, 2007 (2.13 Rev. A)\n\namd64 install cds (5.5, 6.1, 6,2 and all current snapshots from Sept.2006 to April 2007 tested with identical results.\n\nThe output of a rudimentary trace ((w) \"boot\" command as well)after escaping to the loader prompt is:\n\nOK boot -v\nGDB: no debug ports present\nKDB: debugger backends: ddb\nKDB: current backend: ddb\npanic: No BIOS smap info from loader\ncpuid: 0\nKDB: enter: panic\n[thread pid 0 tid 0]\nStopped at kdb_enter+0x2f: nop\ndb\u003e print\nffffffff8047317f\ndb\u003ebt\nTracing pid 0 tid 0 td 0xffffffff8096ff40\nkdb_enter() at kdb_enter+02f\npanic() at panic+0x2f\nhammer_time() at hammer_time+0xd2d\nbtext() at btext+0x24\ndb\u003esmap\n\ndb\u003e\n\nHere is the output of \"lscpi -vxxx\" as \"root\" from a GentooLinux system:\n\n00:00.0 Host bridge: ATI Technologies Inc RS480 Host Bridge (rev 10)\n\tSubsystem: Hewlett-Packard Company Unknown device 280a\n\tFlags: bus master, 66MHz, medium devsel, latency 32\n00: 02 10 50 59 06 01 20 22 10 00 00 06 00 20 00 00\n10: 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00\n20: 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 3c 10 0a 28\n30: 00 00 00 00 c4 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00\n40: 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 42 20 05 00\n50: 3c 10 0a 28 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00\n60: 5f 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 28 00 73 06\n70: e0 08 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 10\n80: 10 0d 00 02 94 14 00 03 20 00 00 00 05 25 00 00\n90: 00 00 00 80 45 cd 45 ed 00 80 00 00 01 00 00 00\na0: 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 0